From: Manuel Bluhm <mbssrc@ssrc.tii.ae>
Subject: [PATCH] script plugin: fix use-after-free crash on keyboard teardown

When the keyboard device is removed during boot (e.g. PCI passthrough
to a VM), the device manager frees the keyboard struct while the script
plugin still holds a stale pointer. Skip the unsafe handler removal and
just null the pointer — the device manager already handles cleanup.

---
 src/plugins/splash/script/plugin.c | 7 +------
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 6 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/plugins/splash/script/plugin.c b/src/plugins/splash/script/plugin.c
index 1234567..abcdefg 100644
--- a/src/plugins/splash/script/plugin.c
+++ b/src/plugins/splash/script/plugin.c
@@ -393,12 +393,7 @@ stop_script_animation (ply_boot_splash_plugin_t *plugin)
                                                           (ply_event_loop_timeout_handler_t)
                                                           on_timeout, plugin);

-        if (plugin->keyboard != NULL) {
-                ply_keyboard_remove_input_handler (plugin->keyboard,
-                                                   (ply_keyboard_input_handler_t)
-                                                   on_keyboard_input);
-                plugin->keyboard = NULL;
-        }
+        plugin->keyboard = NULL;

         script_state_destroy (plugin->script_state);
         script_lib_sprite_destroy (plugin->script_sprite_lib);
